  "body": "Usually, when the user enters or deletes a character in an input field, the `onChange` event is triggered before the `onSelect` event.\n\nHowever, in Internet Explorer, when deleting a character in an input, `onSelect` is triggered BEFORE `onChange`. (When entering a character, we see the correct order of events also in IE.) I could observe this behavior on IE9-11. (I did not test on IE<9.)\n\nAs I understand that React aims at abstracting event handling inconsistencies across different browsers, this seems like an issue that needs fixing.\n\nA jsFiddle demonstrating the issue can be found here: http://jsfiddle.net/kb3gN/8594/\n\nA real-world implementation suffering under this bug, can be found here: http://rawgit.com/effektif/react-mentions/master/examples/index.html (Try using Backspace in IE... I do not see an easy workaround to make this implementation work atm.)\n",
